We need to store 10^15 synapses and 10^11 neurons. We don't want to use graph theory, however, because we prefer a more natural substrate - phext!

https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7058196/

Let's start with the abstraction that every synapse needs a home - a scroll. A total of 10^15 synapses will require either 1000^5 or 100^8 coordinates. We want plenty of room for the exocortex to expand, so let's run with three-digit coordinates.

